    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "12 of 13 V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted because the COU is restricted to quasi-static loading and the single test condition is the standard regulatory benchmark. All three QoIs pass quantitative acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96, percentage difference < 10%) across N=11 specimens from two laboratories. Overall credibility is sufficient for Medium model risk and Medium decision consequence. Package accepted.",
